%N A395838 First differences of A395835.
%C A395838 A395835(n) = M where x^M is the first power of x with a negative coefficient in F(n,x) such that F(n,x) = 1 + x*F(n,x)^2 - x^n*F(n,x)^(2*n), for n >= 2.
%C A395838 Conjecture: this sequence is infinite.
%C A395838 It seems that all positive integers > 1 will appear in this sequence at least once. The frequency of integers 2..32 in this sequence is: [1, 5, 2, 5, 3, 3, 5, 4, 4, 5, 4, 5, 4, 5, 4, 6, 5, 4, 5, 6, 5, 4, 7, 4, 5, 6, 6, 5, 5, 6, 5].
